START OF REACT
1.project setup
npm create vite@latest filename

const App=()=>{
  return(
    <>
    <div>App</div>
    </>
  )
}
export default App

project run => npm run dev

2.Component usage 
single component:

1. src - componenets - filename.jsx - filename must be first letter caps - FileName.jsx
import filename from './path'

Multiple Components:
component inside another componets

App.jsx
import Home from "./components/Home"

const App=()=>{
  return(
    <>
    <div>App</div>
    <Home/>
    </>
  )
}
export default App

Home.jsx
import About from "./About"

const Home = () => {
  return (
    <>
    <div>Home</div>
    <About/>
    </>
  )
}

export default Home

About.jsx
import React from 'react'

const About = () => {
  return (
    <div>About</div>
  )
}

export default About

3.Import and Export in react

2types of import and export methods
1.Export default 
2.Named Export


1.Export defualt
import About from "./About"

const Home = () => {
  return (
    <>
    <div>Home</div>
    <About/>
    </>
  )
}

export default Home

2. Named Export
import React from "react";

const Service = () => {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Service</h2>
    </div>
  );
};

const About = () => {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>About</h1>
      <Service />
    </div>
  );
};

export default About;
export { Service };

TAILWINDCSS in react how to use

npm i tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite => To install tailwindcss

config file => tailwindcss() import
index.css => @import 'tailwindcss'

To create a NAVBAR using Tailwindcss()
import React from 'react'

const App = () => {
  return (
    <>
    <div className='bg-black text-white p-5 flex justify-between '>
      <div>
        <h1>Navbar</h1>
      </div>
      <div className='flex gap-5'>
        <a href="">HOME</a>
        <a href="">ABOUT</a>
        <a href="">SERVICES</a>
        <a href="">CONTACT US</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    </>
  )
}

export default App























